# RiskDetect AI — Environment Variables
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev, or set in the Vercel project dashboard.

## Application
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME=RiskDetect AI

## Auth (login/register UI stays; enforcement is off by default)
# true  → demo user access, no login required (default)
# false → require Supabase login for protected routes
NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_DISABLED=true

## Supabase (Auth + Postgres)
# Local: from `pnpm supabase:start` / `pnpm env:sync`
# Production: Project Settings → API in the Supabase dashboard
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

## OpenAI (AI risk summaries + Security Copilot)
OPENAI_API_KEY=
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

## OCR
# Tesseract.js runs in-process on Node.js serverless (no extra API key).
# Image scan route uses `runtime = "nodejs"` and needs maxDuration ≥ 30–60s.

## Vercel notes
# 1. Set all variables above in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables
# 2. Use Production / Preview / Development as needed
# 3. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL to your Vercel URL (e.g. https://riskdetect.vercel.app)
# 4. In Supabase Auth → URL Configuration, add your Vercel domain to Redirect URLs
# 5. Image uploads are capped at 4MB (Vercel serverless body limit ~4.5MB)
# 6. Hobby plan function timeouts may be too short for heavy OCR — Pro recommended
